Best Practices

Monitor what matters (user-facing symptoms first)
Alert on symptoms, not causes
Reduce alert fatigue (actionable alerts only)
Define SLOs before alerting
Dashboards tell a story
Standardize instrumentation (OpenTelemetry)
Correlate metrics, logs, and traces
Automate remediation where safe
Test your alerts (and your monitoring)
High cardinality awareness (cost/performance)

That spans the conceptual foundation (three pillars, golden signals, RED/USE), the SLO/error-budget framework, alerting and incident management, and the tooling landscape. The highest-leverage starting points are the four golden signals, well-defined SLOs, symptom-based actionable alerts, and correlating metrics/logs/traces — which connects directly to a Prometheus/Grafana/Loki + BetterStack-style stack.